<br>
I'm a level 31 mage, I have been for the last 2 weeks in High Pass Keep camping Pickclaw Goblins with whatever pickup group would have me.  Ocassionally I like to solo a few guards or lookouts.<br>
<br>
I like to camp the Lookout room when bored which is a very slow spawn.  One day I decided to do this, the room was empty (even checked invis).  I took 1 spawn and suddenly 10 min later a warr comes in, he's level 29 and gets right in my face.  he starts saying that I have his spawn and that he was there 4 hours and I have to leave or he will kick my ass or/and petition me.<br>
<br>
The exp gained here is more practicing how to use my pets reather then actual so I would not have had an issue if he was nice about it.  Instead I stayed and enjoyed how pissed off he became.  I tried to share the spawn but he <br>
continued to hurdle insults and make rude jesters he also staye don top of the spawn.  When two spawned at once and was killing him he pleaded for my help which I gave.  Then he wanted bandages.. which I provided.  But he cautiuoned that if I took any kills when they spawned he would petition.<br>
<br>
Eventually bored I left.  I was running and leading a warrior room group soon after which he asked to join.. I let him in.  I never got an apology and he has told other people I am a KSer when I am not.<br>
<br>
Why did I not duel him?<br>
<br>
Why be nice?<br>
<br>
The whiners and complainers about Spawns tend to be either the younger people with no patience and all the time in the world or the older people with no time to power game.  Both tend to hog up the spawns and enforce this bull@#%$ EQ player ethics crap thats basicly protects people that are vocal and know how to bully.  They tend to be the most vocal as well.  I seriously doubt it would be a good idea for me to have stayed or kicked his ass...as it is now necros seem more welcome then mages and that actually hurts since I think we have more to offer a gorup.<br>
<br>
I am tolerated sometimes and always steped on.  When I have defended myself and killed in duels (play on blue server) I have been reported to my guild and told to stop &quot;giving mages a bad name&quot;.  Passed over for loot.  And passed over for groups.  I became a mage knowing this would happen.  When people are different it is our human nature to single them out and perhaps torment them in various ways.  The struggle I have to level my mage is one i take pride in and one i am suceeding with.  One day I will obtain my goal of level 51 and then with Guild help 60 and I will at least be able to destroy the NPCs that have made life so hard (SGs, HGs, Griffs).  I am sure many of those whiney people that called me KSer will have long since stopped playing their char or stopped at a lower level.<br>
<br>
I have always had a policy that I will never start a fight but i will do my best to finish it.  And when I finish a fight I gloat to the world if I win.. and crawl away if I loose.  As it is now I have been put into positions where my honor was at stake just over 10 or 11 times.  I can only rememeber loosing twice.<br>
<br>
Some satisfaction from a bitter Mage.<br>
And I would never have picked another class to be.  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> Happy Necro</span><br> <span class=usertitle>Unregistered User</span><br>   <font color=#333333>(11/24/00 3:21:30 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerrants.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=23.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   I LOVE PNP, here is why</span><hr size=1> PNP was the best thing EVER to be introduced in this game.  I have such a riot with it, I'm serious. I went into Sol B and went into the king room to see if anyone was there.  Well by the rules, you can't camp a spawn, so screw it, I'm hanging out as well.   Soon as that king spawns, I send my pet in who gets first attack.  The other group helps me by trying to steal the kill with their group dmg, but they usually can't overpower me.  The majority of the times, I get the kill and the loot and those there then start to whine how I KS'D them. I just tell them, it's all about PNP baby, I hit it first and it's mine. If you want to call a GM, go for it.  I got a runed cowl the same way.  Got a fbss just for doing first hit and outdamaging the other group on a solo frenzy.  Check this out, I have walked up to an efreeti &quot;camp&quot; and called a guide demanding that I be included in the hunt and the loot.  GM granted my wishes and I won the first pair of boots that dropped since I was there.  Doesn't that just rock?  I mean I love this rule, how can you NOT love it??  Long as I just get first hit, they are stealing from me! I'm level 58, I honestly have did most everything that I have wanted to do, so reputation means little.  I use to think honorable was the way to go, but you know? This changed the rules on us, so hell I'm playing by the rules now and this is perfect for me. I am truly entertained. <br>
<br>
Anyway, I love this rule and have to say that I never had anywhere near the amount of money in my bank or equipment on my twinks before this rule, that I have now.<br>
<br>
I am loving life<br>
